cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation by explicitly modeling target language syntax using CCG supertags. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves improving translation quality, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
